In summary, the sub-baths approach to DMFT has the potential to provide more nuanced insights into correlated electron systems and can function effectively if implemented thoughtfully and rigorously. The key to success lies in clear parameter management, accurate computational methods, and strong testing procedures to ensure the model captures the essential physics as expected. If these aspects are well addressed, the method could lead to significant advancements in understanding complex materials and phenomena.
